Value.value: Ah!  I knew a fellow performer would one day find me! I need a true artist's ear! You, there! Listen to me!
I was once a famous performer! But, never satisfied, I searched and wrote constantly, looking for the perfect song.

One of the songs I wrote, I decided to sing at a ceremony.  I was young and brash, and wished to be famous.  As I began to sing it, to my horror, the ground itself opened up pustules of death, and all within the radius of my song withered and died!
I fled... and I've been trying to build up a new life ever since.  I continued to write songs until recently, when my harp broke.  Now, I just sit here, waiting for a new harp to fall into my lap.

No but to be honest, I came here because I heard of a magical harp possessed by a chieftain of some nearby monsters... legendary in its power.  I haven't been able to locate the damned thing, but I'm not even dressed for battle! Do you think you could find and bring it to me?  I'd be ever so grateful!
Oh thank you!  You've saved me from certain boredom!  Here, take the sonnet I wrote as a reward. But only sing it around enemies!
Ah, so nice of you to visit!  I hope that my song has been of use to you!
Are you still looking for my legendary harp? If it's nearby like the rumors said, maybe you can check those horrible Beastmen!
Hello! I'm looking for skilled bards. Do you know any? Send 'em my way, please!
